; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures UART and receives data.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Connecting ports with a suitable instrument should be correct
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. UART
;    2. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. UART1   : PB11 (Transmit)
;                   : PB10 (Receive)
;
; E. Connection
;    1. PB11 (Transmit / StarterKit 1) <---> PB10 (Recevie / StarterKit 2)
;    2. PB10 (Receive / StarterKit 1) <---> PB11 (Transmit / StarterKit 2)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; UART1
; 1. Channel                   : 1 (UART1)
;
; 2. CLK                       : [ 1 p ]
;    Clock Source              : p (PCLK : Peripheral Clock Source)
;
; 3. Config                    : [ 1 i 8 o 1 38400 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    Data Bit                  : 8 (8bit)
;    Parity                    : o (odd)
;    Stop Bit                  : 1 (1bit)
;    Baudrate                  : 38400 bps
;
; 4. Rx                        : [ 1 8 ]
;    Receive Data Length       : 8
;
; PCU (PBx)
; 1. Port Group                : 1 (PCU Port B)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 1 11 a 4 -pupd p ] [ 1 10 a 4 -pupd p ]
;    Pin Number                : 11 / 10 
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 4 (TX/RX)
;    Pull-up/down              : p (Pull-up)
;
; PCU (PBx)
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 1 11 a 4 -pupd p'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 1 10 a 4 -pupd p'
mpause 30

; UART1
sendln 'cm uart'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'clk 1 p'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 1 i 8 o 1 38400'
mpause 30
sendln 'rx 1 8'
